<br>
As Hermes wandered invisibly among the populace, the word &quot;Grunkar&quot; was mentioned repeatedly.  He noticed that there were a myriad of reactions amongst the folks when these words were mentioned.  But two emotions stood out the most, fear and anger.  Hermes didn't like this at all.  Not knowing can lead to disaster.  And fear and anger often disrupted commerce, and therefore profit.<br>
<br>
Hermes realized that some sleuthing was needed.  And so he decided to head towards the capital.  Maybe he can find King Vasdorf and eavesdrop a bit.<br>
 <p>Hermes the One and Only</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=madmartigan>Madmartigan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 6:47:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Waygarth</span><hr size=1> ::Being the frequent traveler that he was, Madmartigan was currentley visiting the city of Waygarth. He was just coming out of a tavern when he recognised a figure from his travels neer olympus. It was Hermes. Madmartigan walked up to him and pulled him aside. He wispered in his ear so that none elce would hear::<br>
<br>
&quot;The god Hermes. What are you doing way up here?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/umeihao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meihao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 8:39:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Bones Speak</span><hr size=1> Hermes was a bit surprised at seeing Madmartigan here, so far up north.  Hermes has assumed that Madmartigan prefered warmer climates, and even warmer blooded women. But then again, this is Madmartigan.  Madmartigan has always intrigued Hermes, and this was another interesting factoid about Madmartigan that Hermes will remember.  Never underestimate anyone, and never assume, especially when it's Madmartigan.<br>
<br>
And so Hermes took this encounter with Madmartigan as being fortuitious.  After all, Hermes is the God of Fortune, and who better to have fortune smile upon than he who is fortune.<br>
<br>
And so, with a wave of his hand, Hermes transported Madmartigan and himself to one of Hermes's favorite spots, a little pocket of space in the ether.  For some reason, Hermes felt it prudent to be extremely cautious, he wasn't sure who might be listening.<br>
<br>
&quot;Madmartigan, I am glad to have met you in Waygarth.  Why you are this far up north, I will not question.  But I need your wise counsil.  Have you noticed that the people of Waygarth are extremely agitated? The name Grunkar has been whispered everywhere I've been.  The name is familiar, but I can not recall where I have heard it before.  All I know is that it is very important that we find out.  My bones ache, as if they are speaking, warning me that something dreadful is about to occur.  Or it may have occured already!  All I know is this could rock both Heaven and Hell.&quot;<br>
 <p>Hermes the One and Only</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=madmartigan>Madmartigan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 8:51:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.planetkilmer.com/valbum/wil-13.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Bones Speak</span><hr size=1> ::A little startled at the change in scenery, Madmartigan doesnt answer right away. then he speaks::<br>
<br>
&quot;I myself have noticed this change in the people too. I have heard of this Grunkar. From what i have pulled together, it is a force, evil and chaos incarnet in a thing, some sort of person or beast, though i may be wrong. I too feal that something is going to happen. I can tell you that it hasen't happened yet, or i would have known about it, but it is probubly soon to happen. Very soon. It is in great urgencey that we find this force and stop it before it is to late, for i fear that if we dont, then it may cause death and distruction that would make even Hades ponder about stopping it.&quot; <p>Madmartigan- Jokester, trickster, swordsmen, and madman.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/umeihao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meihao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 9:04:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Prisoner</span><hr size=1> &quot;Madmartigan, you are more sane than you let on.  You're right, it is a name of a being of the basest of evil.  But I don't know why it is being brought out again.  Especially way up north.&quot;<br>
<br>
Hermes stops talking for a minute, as his eyes suddenly lose focus.  Something on the mortal realm has sparked his attention.<br>
<br>
&quot;No!!  There has been a sacrifice made in the name of Grunkar!  A human sacrifice!!  But it was performed improperly and a precious human soul has been lost to that demon.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Wait here Madmartigan while I gather this wayward soul and we can question it together.&quot;<br>
<br>
In a blaze of immortal fury, Hermes departs.  And just as suddenly he reappears, but this time, not alone.  He has with him, chained and bound a wraith.  Usually Hermes treats souls with tender care, but in this case, Hermes has this one, bound as if it were a prisoner.  And it truth it is.<br>
<br>
&quot;Madmartigan, this dispicable creature is a lost soul.  He gave himself FREELY, and for that I can not commend him to Hades.  I only have a limited time before even I will lose control of it.  Quickly, we must unearth as much information as we can from this pitiful insect.&quot;<br>
<br>
With eyes of unbridled fury, Hermes turns to the soul.  But instead of fear, Hermes and Madmartigan sees triumph written on its face.  It knows that wherever he is going, neither Madmartigan nor Hermes can follow.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/umeihao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meihao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 11:30:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Prisoner</span><hr size=1> But before any of them could question the prisoner, the wraith began to scream, the kind of scream only the eternally tormented and damned could manage.<br>
<br>
&quot;Are you doing this?&quot; asks Madmartigan, as he watched in fascination.<br>
<br>
Hermes shook his head.  &quot;I may be angry, but even I wouldn't torment the dead.  This creature's pain is not my doing.&quot;<br>
<br>
As they watched, the wraith screamed out with even more agony.  Suddenly, as if invisible claws were tearing it to shreds, the wraith flew into hundreds of gossamyr pieces.<br>
<br>
&quot;By all that's holy, may you find peace&quot; prayed Hermes.  His heart saddened by what had occurred.<br>
<br>
&quot;Enough, we can't let this atrocity continue.  We must find out more about this.  I suggest, Madmartigan, that we split up.  Enlist as many others as we can.  I don't think we can do this alone.  Maybe the Oracle in Thebes can be of help.&quot;<br>
<br>
Madmartigan, brandishing his Rune Blade, whispered the mystical words that would allow him to traverse the multiverse, silently disappeared in a plume of darkness.<br>
<br>
Hermes looks around at the now empty void.  Once again, it looks like the balance of Life has once again been disturbed.  Before he too disappeared, his final thought was &quot;But will this be the last?&quot;<br>
 <p>Hermes the One and Only</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=madmartigan>Madmartigan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 11:36:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.planetkilmer.com/valbum/wil-13.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> calling all gods!!</span><hr size=1> ::Madmartigan shows up at the base of mount olympus::<br>
