<br>
::He is speaking fast and is almost unintelligable::<br>
<br>
&quot;We need to get the best warriors Waygarth. Theres something going down that could be catistrophic. The Fear and panic that is going down in the peoples of Waygarth's minds is unbeleavable. Something very bad is about to happen, and we need to stop it NOW!!&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/29/01 1:03:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The explanation</span><hr size=1> ::arrives and looks around frantically:: whats going on? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/umeihao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meihao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/29/01 1:44:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Grunkar</span><hr size=1> Hermes appears suddenly, looking haggard and very agitated.<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank you all for being here.  I have very dire news.  I had gone to Qrendril, the Tree of Time, and I traced the name Grunkar.  It's very very bad.&quot;<br>
<br>
Looking around them, Hermes decided that it wasn't even safe talking about this even here at the base Mt. Olympus.   And so he wrote in the air, a fiery runic symbol, and suddenly an irredescent bubble surrounded those gathered.<br>
<br>
&quot;I hope this will be enough.  What I am about to tell you is very important.  The reason so much security is needed is because the demon we're dealing with has agents all around us.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;At the Tree, the Tree Hag informed me that Grunkar was actually one of the progenitors of the Titans.  As Chronus is the progenitor of Zeus, Hera, Poseidon, and Hades.  So too is Grunkar one of the progenitors of the Titans.  When the Titans were banished into Tartarus, so too had the Titans banished Grunkar in eons past.  It seems the last time the Titans had escaped, they had awakened Grunkar.  But he is only semi-conscious, only his astral self is aware, his body is still trapped.  That is why I am so scared about talking out in the open.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;It seems that acolytes of Grunkar has been amassing up north, in Waygarth.  Their failed attempt at a human sacrifice indicates that they are still disorganized.  And this gives us hope.  Some of us has to deal with the acolytes, and some has to deal with the chaos they have already wrecked.&quot;<br>
<br>
Then Hermes hesitates, as he prepares himself to utter the next sentence.<br>
<br>
&quot;And some of us have to brave the nightmares of Tartarus to deal with Grunkar and his minions.&quot;<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/29/01 2:29:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grunkar</span><hr size=1> I feel so awful.because I want to help and everything..but I have now idea how to fight.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=madmartigan>Madmartigan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/29/01 2:47:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.planetkilmer.com/valbum/wil-13.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A volunteer for Tartarus</span><hr size=1> ::Madmartigan steps forward and speaks in an unshaken voice, filled with bravery and courage never before seen in this man.::<br>
<br>
&quot;Hermes, i will face the horrors. If it means keeping peace in the world, then i would stay in Tartarus forever. I shall go.&quot;<br>
<br>
::His statement is bold and true.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/umeihao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meihao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/29/01 3:27:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Proud</span><hr size=1> Hermes smiles proudly at his friends.  None them, including himself realize what kind of horrors and trials they will be facing.  Yet, here they stand, ready to fight to the last, if need be.  His heart sang with pride, but he became saddened because there was a definite chance that they may never see each other again.<br>
<br>
&quot;Good.  But before we do, we need to fid out more about Grunkar.  Stopping him will not be easy.  And we still don't know who else may be involved.  So before we act, we need to disperse and do some detective work.&quot;<br>
<br>
With a quick blow, Hermes dissipated the rune, and the bubble disappeared.  Hoping that this will not be the last time they are together, Hermes fades away slowly.<br>
